ce:section.ce:para:
To verify the feasibility of PNFs for fluorescent detection of ferric ion in real water, the emission spectra of PNF (0.125 mg mL‒1) aqueous solutions without and with FN (5 μM) were collected as shown in Fig. 6
                        . There are slight deviations between spectra for PNFs in real water and spectra for PNFs in distilled water, probably due to the influence of impurity ions in real water. The concentrations of ferric ion in real water can be estimated (Table 2
                        ), according to the standard curves of PL intensity of PNF aqueous solutions as a function of FN concentration. The close detection values and the small standard deviations based on three parallel tests confirm the feasibility of PNFs for fluorescent detection of ferric ion in real water.
